  "body": "- [X] I've [opened a support ticket](https://trufflesuite.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/requests/new) before filing this issue. (Ticket: 521615)\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nThe default recommended configuration for mainnet is not provided in `truffle-config`, so it leads to misconfiguration.\r\n\r\nI used the old style configuration parameter, gas/gasprice, which works fine for both the local development environment and the Rinkeby network. However, it now does not work on Mainnet with EIP 1559 support.\r\n\r\nUsing the gas/gasprice parameter, contract deployment can be done, but strange errors occur during console interactions, even for read-only function calls.\r\n\r\nThe only way to interact properly is to replace the parameters with maxFeePerGas/maxPriorityFeePerGas for Type 2 transactions.\r\n\r\nSo, I suggest to give the default mainnet configuration parameters in `truffle-config` , rather than just mentioning them in your online documentation.\r\n\r\nFinally, one more suggestion: Due to the unstable gas state of the ethereum network, predefining a fixed amount of gas may cause network confirmation timeouts, so I suggest providing a fastest/most economical parameter so that Truffle can prioritize the fastest or most economical way to complete contracts when deploying them.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
